District, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Pershore, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, England"},"en":{"Abt 1228–":"about 1228–Deceased","1229–Female":"1229–Deceased","1253–1318":"1253–1318","1228–Male":"1228–Deceased","1228":"1228","1253":"1253","1318":"1318","Abt 1228":"about 1228","1229":"1229","Pershore, Wychavon District, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","Pershore, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Walter","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin), German, Dutch, Polish, Swedish, and Danish: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This personal name was introduced into England both in the reign of Edward the Confessor and by the Normans (in the forms <i>Walt(i)er</i>, <i>Waut(i)er</i>). After the Norman Conquest it soon became one of the most popular personal names in Britain. Compare   Walther  .","Germanized or Americanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Valter</b> and Czech <b>Valtr</b>: from the personal name <i>Valter</i>, <i>Valtr</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see 1 above)."],"variants":[{"name":"Walthers","meanings":["German: patronymic from the personal name <i>Walther</i> (see   Walter  )."]},{"name":"McQuate","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uait</b> ‘son of <i>Uat</i>’, Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Wat</i>, a short form of   Walter  . Compare the Irish form   McQuaid  ."]},{"name":"Waltke","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Jurgen, Wilhelmina.","German: from a pet form of any of the ancient Germanic personal names formed with Old High German <i>waltan</i> ‘to rule’ as the first element, as in   Walter  ."]},{"name":"McWaters","meanings":["Scottish and northern Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uaitéir</b>, a patronymic from a Gaelicized form of the personal name   Walter  , with excrescent English <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Wahler","meanings":["German:","from the personal name <i>Wol(d)er</i>, Low German form of   Walter  .","habitational name for someone from any of various places called Wahl, Wahle, or Wahlen."]},{"name":"McWalter","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: from Gaelic <b>Mac Uaitéir</b> ‘son of   Walter  ’."]},{"name":"Walters","meanings":["English: variant of   Walter  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","German: patronymic from   Walter  ."]},{"name":"McQuaid","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Colum, Nuala.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Uaid</b> ‘son of <i>Uad</i>’, Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Wat</i>, a short form of   Walter  . Compare the Scottish form   McQuate  ."]},{"name":"Walther","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Hans, Erwin, Wolfgang, Otto, Gerhard, Gunter, Heinz, Klaus, Konrad, Bernd, Bernhard.","German, Dutch, Swedish, and Danish: variant of   Walter  ."]},{"name":"Lauter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ernst, Erwin, Kurt, Sigismund, Wolf.","German: topographic name and habitational name, from a common stream name meaning ‘clear’, from Middle High German <i>hlutra</i>, or from any of the places called Lauter or Lauta (Saxony). This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine) and some other European countries.","Germanized or Americanized form of Slovenian <b>Lavtar</b> or its Croatized and rare Slovenian variant <b>Lautar</b>: from a dialect variant of the personal name <i>Valter</i> (see   Walter  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Walter was born about 1228, in Pershore, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Dama Walter."},"et":{"Abt 1228–":"umbes 1228–Surnud","1229–Female":"1229–Surnud","1253–1318":"1253–1318","1228–Male":"1228–Surnud","1228":"1228","1253":"1253","1318":"1318","Abt 1228":"umbes 1228","1229":"1229","Pershore, Wychavon District, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pershore, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1228–":"noin 1228–Kuollut","1229–Female":"1229–Kuollut","1253–1318":"1253–1318","1228–Male":"1228–Kuollut","1228":"1228","1253":"1253","1318":"1318","Abt 1228":"noin 1228","1229":"1229","Pershore, Wychavon District, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pershore, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1228–":"environ 1228–Décédé","1229–Female":"1229–Décédée","1253–1318":"1253–1318","1228–Male":"1228–Décédé","1228":"1228","1253":"1253","1318":"1318","Abt 1228":"environ 1228","1229":"1229","Pershore, Wychavon District, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Pershore, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Walter est né environ 1228, à Pershore, Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Dama Walter."},"de":{"Abt 1228–":"um 1228–Verstorben","1229–Female":"1229–Verstorben","1253–1318":"1253–1318","1228–Male":"1228–Verstorben","1228":"1228","1253":"1253","1318":"1318","Abt 1228":"um 1228","1229":"1229","Pershore, Wychavon District, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, Eng